  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR Global Health Research Group on Evidence to Policy Pathway to Immunisation in China (NIHR EPIC)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A UK and low- and middle-income country (LMIC) partnership that aims to conduct applied vaccine research to help decision makers build a vaccination programme that ensures reliable, affordable, equitable and uninterrupted supply of vaccines to the poorest and most at-risk members of the population.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR Global Health Research Group on Evidence to Policy Pathway to Immunisation in China (NIHR EPIC) objectives: 1) Conduct research to inform vaccination policy in China, focused around three themes: (i) understanding the epidemiology and burden of vaccine-preventable diseases, (ii) understanding manufacturing capacity, public demand and confidence around vaccines, and (iii) modelling the health, economic and equity impact of vaccine strategies, particularly on vulnerable populations. 2) Use results in collaboration with key stakeholders to strengthen the evidence-to-policy pathway for immunisation in China (and eventually other countries). 3) Set up a cross-national and cross-sectoral collaboration between four British and Chinese public health and academic organisations: the London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine (LSHTM), Public Health England (PHE), Chinese Centre for Disease Control and Prevention (China CDC) and Fudan University (Fudan).</narrative>
  </description>
